x4freetext: LANSCE/WNR facility.
800-MeV protons on natural tungsten.
Centroid of neutron energy distribution and standard
deviation of neutron-energy distribution given.
93.2% enriched 235U sample, arial density 0.617 g/cm2,
encased in plastic laminate. Sample contained 5.4%
GEANIE array of 11 Compton-suppressed planar
detectors, 9 Compton-suppressed and 6 unsuppressed
coaxial detectors. Recorded prompt, singlefold, and
higher-fold events.
Fission chamber containing both 235U and 238U used as
flux monitor.
Gamma ray spectrum fitted using code XGAM.
Normalized using ENDF/B-VI up to
16 MeV, to Lisowski from 16-100 MeV, and to Goldanskii
above 100 MeV.

x4codes.shortRef: Conf: Conf.on Nucl.Data For Sci.and Technol.,Mito 1988, p.97 (1988)
Jour: Zhurnal Eksperimental`noi i Teoret. Fiziki, Vol.29, p.778 (1955)

x4freetext: Corrected for background and deadtime.
Several caveats apply to data:
1. Fraction of yields that go down to ground-state band
is not known in general.
2. Angular distribution of emitted gammas could not be
systematically measured, and could introduce a
reduction of up to 15% in the extracted yields.
3. Gamma ray counts are extracted from very complex
spectra, and there is a chance that any single line
may be contaminated, misidentified, or that its
inferred yield may be incorrect due to a poor fit.
